    <!-- Application Structure Plan: Dashboard-First approach. 
         1. Header: Quick context (Trainer, Goal).
         2. Analytics Dashboard: Visualizes the balance of the training (Bloom distribution & Method mix) to validate pedagogical quality.
         3. Control Center: Filters and the specific "No Power" Toggle to switch contexts.
         4. Interactive Timeline: The main flow. Cards represent time slots. They expand for details. They react to the "No Power" toggle by swapping content.
         5. Evaluation Grid: Static reference for success criteria.
         This structure helps the trainer visualize the day's flow and instantly access the backup plan. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
         1. Bloom Taxonomy -> Goal: Balance Check -> Viz: Doughnut Chart (Chart.js) -> Interaction: Tooltip -> Standard distribution viz.
         2. Teaching Methods -> Goal: Method Mix -> Viz: Bar Chart (Chart.js) -> Interaction: Tooltip -> Comparison of active vs passive time.
         3. Timeline Items -> Goal: Schedule Flow -> Viz: Card List -> Interaction: Expansion & Content Swap (Digital/Analog) -> Clear readability.
         4. Evaluation Criteria -> Goal: Checklist -> Viz: Styled HTML Table -> Interaction: None -> Clean reference. 
         CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
